The paper is about learning-to-rank models, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) tasks. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes new loss functions and models that use neural networks, gradient boosting, and regression trees, which are common techniques in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), suggesting cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.CL as likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses datasets that include text and images, indicating that cs.CV is also a possible sub-category.
